## Step 7
Now, to find the percentage of patients with low blood pressure and a regular heartbeat, we first note that 19% have low blood pressure. We've calculated that 3.9% have low blood pressure and an irregular heartbeat. Thus, the percentage with low blood pressure and a regular heartbeat = 19% - 3.9% = 15.1%.

