Problem: Draw one card at random from a standard deck of cards. The sample space $S$ is the collection of the 52 cards. Assume that the probability set function assigns $1 / 52$ to each of the 52 outcomes. Let
$$
\begin{aligned}
A & =\{x: x \text { is a jack, queen, or king }\}, \\
